GAL22V10
ROM_YM

PHI2 A15 A14 A13 A12 A11 A0 RW HALT IOA0 IOA1 GND
IOA2 IOA3 ROMA14 ROMA15 ROMA16 ROMA17 ROMCE BC1 BDIR PHI2OUT YMLE VCC

PHI2OUT = PHI2
BDIR = /A15 * /A14 * /A13 * /A12 * A11 * /RW * HALT * PHI2
BC1 = /A15 * /A14 * /A13 * /A12 * A11 * /RW * /A0 * HALT * PHI2
YMLE = /A15 * /A14 * /A13 * /A12 * A11 * /RW * HALT * PHI2
/ROMCE = A15 * RW + /A15 * A14 * RW
ROMA14 = A15 * A14 + /A15 * IOA0
ROMA15 = A15 + IOA1
ROMA16 = A15 + IOA2
ROMA17 = A15 + IOA3

DESCRIPTION

Atari 7800 YM2149 decoder + bank mapper (32-pin board, ATF22V10).
YM mapped to $0800/$0801 (A15=0, A14=0, A13=0, A12=0, A11=1).
  $0800 (A0=0): address register  BDIR=1, BC1=1, YMLE=1
  $0801 (A0=1): data register     BDIR=1, BC1=0, YMLE=1

SuperGame-style fixed + banked ROM layout:
  $8000-$FFFF fixed 32KB  -> top of chip (ROMA17:A15 forced high,
                             ROMA14 = console A14)
  $4000-$7FFF banked 16KB -> bank N = YM IOA[3:0] (ROMA17:A14)
ROM enabled for reads across $4000-$FFFF (RW gating prevents bus
contention on writes; ROM OE is hardwired low on the board).

YM IOA0-IOA3 are PLD inputs with 10k pull-ups. Write YM reg 7
bit 6 = 1 (IOA output), then reg 14 = 16KB bank number:
  AT27C010 128KB: banks 0-5 free (6,7 = fixed region)
  AT27C020 256KB: banks 0-13 free (14,15 = fixed region)
  AT27C040 512KB: pin 31/A18 tied VCC, top half only, as 27C020
Power-on: IOA is Hi-Z, pull-ups select bank 15 (a mirror of the
fixed region). Vectors/boot code live in the fixed bank, so no
code duplication across banks is needed.
